    <stitle>EC-16 CONTROLLER - TROUBLESHOOTING - TESTING THE WHEEL SPEED SENSOR, PART A</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl0403220" svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="1">
        <title>TESTING THE WHEEL SPEED SENSOR, PART A</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0403211">Figure 11</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0403211" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0403211" filename="../figg04/G0403211.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 11. Testing the Wheel Speed Sensor, Part A</caption>
        </figure>
        <table id="hl0403229">
            <title>Testing the Wheel Speed Sensor, Part A</title>
            <tgroup cols="5">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.86in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.87in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" colwidth="1.38in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" colwidth="1.28in"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="5" spanname="s1t5"/>
                <thead>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>With ignition ON, note illuminated LEDs. Do magnetic RESET and note reaction of red
                                LEDs. Second time to this point during testing?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>Go to
                                <hotlnk document="s04032_HL0403230.xml" xrefid="hl0403230">TESTING THE WHEEL SPEED
                                    SENSOR, PART B</hotlnk>, and begin testing.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Any red LEDs ON?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>Go to Step 4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Turn ignition OFF and check the items in Wheel Speed Sensor Checklist below. Reconnect
                                connectors at EC-16 and speed sensor, and do magnetic RESET. Note red LEDs. Are any red
                                LEDs illuminated?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>Go to
                                <hotlnk document="s04032_HL0403232.xml" xrefid="hl0403232">INSPECTION FOR ILLUMINATED
                                    LEDS, PART II</hotlnk>.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Go to
                                <hotlnk document="s04032_HL0403208.xml" xrefid="hl0403208">INITIAL START-UP
                                    PROCEDURE</hotlnk>.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Same red LEDs ON?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4">
                            <para>Go to
                                <hotlnk document="s04032_HL0403230.xml" xrefid="hl0403230">TESTING THE WHEEL SPEED
                                    SENSOR, PART B</hotlnk>, and begin testing.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5">
                            <para>Go to
                                <hotlnk document="s04032_HL0403214.xml" xrefid="hl0403214">INSPECTION FOR ILLUMINATED
                                    LEDS, PART III</hotlnk>, and retest.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
        <para>Wheel Speed Sensor Checklist</para>
        <seqlist style="alphauc">
            <item>
                <para>Check "gap" between speed sensor and exciter or tone ring (gap for Bendix WS-20 speed sender is
                    between 0 and .015 inch). If sensor gap must be adjusted, check for loose or worn wheel bearings
                    before re-gapping sensor. Refer to vehicle maintenance manual for worn bearings.
                </para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>If sensor gap is correct, check wheel bearing for free play to verify it complies with
                    manufacturer's recommendations.
                </para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Make certain exciter or tone ring is in place and inspect condition. Check for missing or damaged
                    teeth and that it runs true and perpendicular to sensor face.
                </para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Check wiring harness and connectors that run to sensor.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Check for dragging brakes (over-adjusted, trapped air in actuator, out of round drums, faulty
                    return springs, parking brake system faults, etc.) and correct and retest.
                </para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
    </svcproc>
